9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 376, L.D. 843, “An Act to Continue
10 Funding for the Health Insurance Consumer Assistance Program”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
12 'Sec. 2. Transfers from available fiscal year 2025-26 and fiscal year 2026-
13 27 Department of Professional and Financial Regulation, Bureau of Insurance
14 Other Special Revenue Funds balances to Department of Attorney General.
15 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, on November 1, 2025 and on July 1,
16 2026, the State Controller shall transfer $300,000 from available balances in the Bureau of
17 Insurance Other Special Revenue Funds account within the Department of Professional and
18 Financial Regulation to the Department of the Attorney General, Administration - Attorney
19 General, Other Special Revenue Funds account.'
20 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
21 'Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
22 allocations are made.
23 ATTORNEY GENERAL, DEPARTMENT OF THE
24 Administration - Attorney General 0310
25 Initiative: Provides a one-time allocation to contract with a designated nonprofit,
26 independent health insurance consumer assistance entity to continue to operate the Health
27 Insurance Consumer Assistance Program, as established in the Maine Revised Statutes,
28 Title 24-A, section 4326.
29 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
30 All Other $300,000 $300,000
31 __________ __________
32 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $300,000 $300,000
