COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 376, L.D. 843
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, requires that the
55 continued funding in the bill to support the Health Insurance Consumer Assistance Program
66 must be provided through a transfer of available Other Special Revenue Funds balances
77 from the Department of Professional and Financial Regulation, Bureau of Insurance Other
88 Special Revenue Funds account to the Department of the Attorney General, Administration
99 - Attorney General, Other Special Revenue Funds account.
